ents exponential backoff with jitter\n583: - Retryable returns last error on failure\n584: - `EventuallyRetryable(actual, timeout, pollingInterval, maxRetries)` wrapper exists\n585: - Retryable respects context cancellation\n586: - Unit tests verify retry behavior\n587: - Unit tests verify backoff calculation\n588: - Integration test uses Retryable for known flaky operation\n589: - `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Retry` passes\n590: \n591: **Dependencies:** T-1.6  \n592: **Estimated Time:** 1.5 hours\n593: \n594: ---\n595: \n596: ### 5.3 Implement Timeout Management Utilities\n597: \n598: **Task ID:** T-5.3  \n599: **Description:** Implement timeout context utilities for test operations\n600: \n601: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/timeout.go`\n602: \n603: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n604: - `TimeoutContext(timeout) (ctx, cancel)` function exists\n605: - `WithDefaultTimeout() (ctx, cancel)` function exists (5 minute default)\n606: - Timeout contexts log when timeout occurs\n607: - Cancel functions clean up resources properly\n608: - Timeout contexts handle nested timeouts correctly\n609: - Unit tests verify timeout behavior\n610: - Unit tests verify cancellation behavior\n611: - Integration test demonstrates timeout handling\n612: - `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Timeout` passes\n613: \n614: **Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n615: **Estimated Time:** 1 hour\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ### 5.4 Implement Test Reporting\n620: \n621: **Task ID:** T-5.4  \n622: **Description:** Implement custom test reporting with multiple output formats\n623: \n624: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/reporting.go`\n625: \n626: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n627: - `TestReporter` struct exists with outputPath field\n628: - `Report(report)` method exists\n629: - `generateHTMLReport(reportData)` generates HTML report\n630: - `generateJSONReport(reportData)` generates JSON report\n631: - `generateJUnitReport(reportData)` generates JUnit XML report\n632: - Reports include: summary, specs, duration, pass/