{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897045611,"sessionID":"ses_284500342ffe3Yogb7xdZXscIa","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb66a39001OWO7ZROkM6uikU","messageID":"msg_d7bb5ed42001JMhTuWnRSi75cq","sessionID":"ses_284500342ffe3Yogb7xdZXscIa","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d6e868d48da2443e9dfc12303fbd9caf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# E2E Integration Tests\n\nThis directory contains comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube project. The E2E test suite validates the complete system behavior by deploying a real or simulated Kubernetes environment, creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, and verifying end-to-end workflows.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe E2E test suite covers:\n\n- **AgentRuntime E2E Tests**: Test creation, invocation, lifecycle management, and error handling for AgentRuntime resources\n- **CodeInterpreter E2E Tests**: Test creation, code execution, file operations, and error handling for CodeInterpreter resources\n- **Integration Tests**: Test cross-component workflows, session management, scalability, and error recovery\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── framework/              # Test framework infrastructure\n│   ├── framework.go       # Core framework setup and Kubernetes client management\n│   ├── helpers.go         # Helper utilities for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter operations\n│   ├── assertions.go      # Custom Gomega matchers for assertions\n│   ├── fixtures.go        # Test fixtures and data generators\n│   ├── timeout.go         # Timeout management utilities\n│   ├── retry.go           # Retry logic utilities\n│   └── failure_handler.go # Test failure handling and diagnostics collection\n├── agentruntime/          # AgentRuntime E2E tests\n│   └── agentruntime_suite_test.go\n├── codeinterpreter/       # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\n│   └── codeinterpreter_suite_test.go\n├── integration/           # Integration tests\n│   └── integration_suite_test.go\n├── manifests/             # Test manifests\n│   ├── agentruntimes/\n│   ├── codeinterpreters/\n│   └── deployments/\n└── reports/               # Test reports and diagnostics\n    └── diagnostics/\n```\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Go 1.25 or later\n- kind, minikube, or k3s for Kubernetes cluster\n- kubectl for cluster management\n- Docker for container images\n- Ginkgo v2 and Gomega for testing\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Clone the repository:\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube.git\ncd agentcube\n```\n\n2. Install dependencies:\n```bash\ngo mod download\ngo install github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2/ginkgo@latest\n```\n\n3. Build the project:\n```bash\nmake build\n```\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Local Development with kind\n\n1. Create a kind cluster:\n```bash\nkind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n2. Load Docker images:\n```bash\nkind load docker-image agentcube:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-workload-manager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n3. Deploy AgentCube:\n```bash\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n```\n\n4. Wait for deployment:\n```bash\nkubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n    deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n```\n\n5. Run E2E tests:\n```bash\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n```\n\n### Running Specific Test Suites\n\n```bash\n# Run AgentRuntime tests only\ngo test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run CodeInterpreter tests only\ngo test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/ -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run integration tests only\ngo test ./test/e2e/integration/ -v -ginkgo.v\n```\n\n### Running Specific Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run tests matching a pattern\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.focus=\"AgentRuntime Creation\"\n\n# Run tests with verbose output\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -ginkgo.showNodeEvents\n\n# Run tests with skip cleanup\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -skip-cleanup=true\n```\n\n### Running Tests with Options\n\n```bash\n# Run tests with race detector\ngo test -race ./test/e2e/...\n\n# Run tests with coverage\ngo test -cover ./test/e2e/...\ngo test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./test/e2e/...\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n\n# Run tests with custom timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -timeout 30m\n```\n\n## Test Organization\n\n### Framework Layer\n\nThe test framework provides:\n\n- **TestFramework**: Core framework with Kubernetes client initialization, namespace management, and cleanup\n- **AgentRuntimeHelper**: Utilities for AgentRuntime CRUD operations, session management, and invocation\n- **CodeInterpreterHelper**: Utilities for CodeInterpreter CRUD operations, code execution, and file operations\n- **Custom Assertions**: Gomega matchers for common assertions (BeReady, HaveSessionID, etc.)\n- **Fixtures**: Test data generators for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and request/response payloads\n- **Timeout Management**: Utilities for creating timeout contexts with logging\n- **Retry Logic**: Utilities for retrying flaky operations with exponential backoff\n- **Failure Handler**: Automatic diagnostic collection on test failures (pod logs, resource status, events)\n\n### Test Categories\n\n#### AgentRuntime Tests\n\n- **Creation Tests**: Verify AgentRuntime creation, default values, and readiness\n- **Invocation Tests**: Verify session creation, invocation, and concurrent invocations\n- **Lifecycle Tests**: Verify session expiration and deletion\n- **Error Handling Tests**: Verify invalid spec rejection, non-existent session handling, and malformed payload handling\n- **Concurrent Access Tests**: Verify concurrent session creations\n\n#### CodeInterpreter Tests\n\n- **Creation Tests**: Verify CodeInterpreter creation, default values, and readiness\n- **Execution Tests**: Verify code execution, syntax error handling, runtime error handling, and state preservation\n- **File Operations Tests**: Verify file upload, download, and large file handling\n- **Error Handling Tests**: Verify invalid spec rejection and malformed code handling\n- **Concurrent Access Tests**: Verify concurrent code executions\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- **Workflow Tests**: Verify complete workflows (creation → session → invocation → deletion)\n- **Cross-Resource Tests**: Verify AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter interaction\n- **Session Management Tests**: Verify multiple sessions for the same resource\n- **Scalability Tests**: Verify concurrent resource creation (10 AgentRuntimes, 10 CodeInterpreters)\n- **Resource Cleanup Tests**: Verify proper resource cleanup\n- **Error Recovery Tests**: Verify recovery from session failures\n\n## Writing New Tests\n\n### Test Structure\n\nUse Ginkgo's BDD-style structure:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Feature Name\", func() {\n    var (\n        f      *framework.TestFramework\n        helper *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper\n        ctx    context.Context\n        cancel context.CancelFunc\n    )\n\n    BeforeSuite(func() {\n        f = framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"test-name\")\n        ctx, cancel = context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 15*time.Minute)\n        defer cancel()\n\n        Expect(f.Setup(ctx)).To(Succeed())\n        Eventually(func() bool {\n            return f.AgentCubeReady()\n        }, 10*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n\n        helper = framework.NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f)\n    })\n\n    AfterSuite(func() {\n        if f != nil && !f.Options().SkipCleanup {\n            Expect(f.Cleanup()).To(Succeed())\n        }\n    })\n\n    Context(\"Specific Context\", func() {\n        It(\"should do something\", func() {\n            // Test implementation\n        })\n    })\n})\n```\n\n### Using Helpers\n\n```go\n// Create AgentRuntime\nart := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-art\")\nart.Namespace = f.Namespace()\ncreated, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n// Wait for ready\nerr = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n// Create session\nreq := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, f.Namespace())\nresp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n// Invoke session\npayload := framework.NewTestInvokePayloadWithString(\"hello\")\ninvokeResp, err := helper.InvokeSession(ctx, resp.SessionID, payload, nil)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\nExpect(invokeResp.StatusCode).To(Equal(200))\n\n// Delete session\nerr = helper.DeleteSession(ctx, resp.SessionID)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n```\n\n### Using Custom Assertions\n\n```go\n// Verify resource is ready\nEventually(func() bool {\n    art, _ := helper.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, art.Name)\n    for _, condition := range art.Status.Conditions {\n        if condition.Type == \"Ready\" && condition.Status == metav1.ConditionTrue {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n\n// Verify response has session ID\nExpect(resp).To(HaveSessionID())\n\n// Verify code execution succeeded\nExpect(execResp).To(SucceedWithoutError())\nExpect(execResp).To(HaveExitCode(0))\nExpect(execResp).To(HaveStdout(\"expected output\"))\n```\n\n## Debugging Failed Tests\n\n### Viewing Diagnostics\n\nWhen a test fails, diagnostics are automatically collected and saved to `test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/`:\n\n- `<test-name>-<pod-name>.log`: Pod logs\n- `<test-name>-<timestamp>.json`: Resource status and events\n\n### Manual Debugging\n\n1. Check test namespace:\n```bash\nkubectl get pods -n e2e-test-<random>\nkubectl get agentruntimes -n e2e-test-<random>\nkubectl get codeinterpreters -n e2e-test-<random>\n```\n\n2. View pod logs:\n```bash\nkubectl logs -n e2e-test-<random> <pod-name>\n```\n\n3. View resource status:\n```bash\nkubectl describe agentruntime <name> -n e2e-test-<random>\nkubectl describe codeinterpreter <name> -n e2e-test-<random>\n```\n\n4. View events:\n```bash\nkubectl get events -n e2e-test-<random>\n```\n\n### Common Issues\n\n- **Cluster not ready**: Ensure AgentCube deployment is ready before running tests\n- **Image not found**: Load Docker images into the cluster\n- **Timeout**: Increase test timeout with `-timeout` flag\n- **Resource not found**: Check resource names and namespace\n\n## Performance Testing\n\n### Load Testing\n\nThe integration tests include load testing scenarios:\n\n- 10 concurrent AgentRuntime creations\n- 10 concurrent CodeInterpreter creations\n- 10 concurrent invocations\n\n### Performance Baselines\n\nSee `test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md` for performance baselines and acceptable ranges.\n\n## CI/CD Integration\n\nThe E2E tests are integrated with GitHub Actions (see `.github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml`):\n\n```yaml\n- Run tests on push to main/develop branches\n- Run tests on pull requests\n- Upload test results and diagnostics as artifacts\n- Timeout: 30 minutes\n```\n\n## Test Patterns\n\nSee `test/e2e/PATTERNS.md` for common test patterns and best practices.\n\n## Running Tests Guide\n\nSee `test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md` for detailed step-by-step instructions.\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen adding new tests:\n\n1. Follow the existing test structure and patterns\n2. Use the framework helpers and fixtures\n3. Add appropriate assertions\n4. Test both success and failure paths\n5. Ensure tests are independent and can run in parallel\n6. Add documentation for new test cases\n\n## License\n\nThis code is licensed under the Apache License 2.0.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go\">\nERROR [23:2] could not import k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime (no required module 