{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897086043,"sessionID":"ses_284500342ffe3Yogb7xdZXscIa","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb70830001b3zQU41BgyJ0t0","messageID":"msg_d7bb66ac5001dU5Ee4imUdaPD7","sessionID":"ses_284500342ffe3Yogb7xdZXscIa","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-075d56d82bbf433a952e9df04079769b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Running E2E Tests - Step-by-Step Guide\n\nThis guide provides detailed step-by-step instructions for running E2E tests for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)\n- [Local Development Setup](#local-development-setup)\n- [Running Tests](#running-tests)\n- [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n- [Test Results Interpretation](#test-results-interpretation)\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n### Required Tools\n\n- **Go 1.25 or later**: [Download](https://golang.org/dl/)\n- **kind 0.20.0 or later**: `go install sigs.k8s.io/kind@latest`\n- **kubectl**: `curl -LO \"https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl\"`\n- **Docker**: [Download](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop)\n- **Ginkgo**: `go install github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2/ginkgo@latest`\n\n### Verification\n\n```bash\n# Check Go version\ngo version\n\n# Check kind version\nkind version\n\n# Check kubectl version\nkubectl version --client\n\n# Check Docker version\ndocker --version\n\n# Check Ginkgo version\nginkgo version\n```\n\n## Local Development Setup\n\n### Step 1: Clone Repository\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube.git\ncd agentcube\n```\n\n### Step 2: Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\ngo mod download\n```\n\n### Step 3: Build Project\n\n```bash\nmake build\n```\n\n### Step 4: Create kind Cluster\n\n```bash\n# Create a kind cluster named agentcube-e2e\nkind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Verify cluster is running\nkubectl cluster-info --context kind-agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n### Step 5: Load Docker Images\n\n```bash\n# Load AgentCube images into the cluster\nkind load docker-image agentcube:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-workload-manager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-picod:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Verify images are loaded\ndocker exec agentcube-e2e-control-plane crictl images | grep agentcube\n```\n\n### Step 6: Deploy AgentCube\n\n```bash\n# Apply CRDs\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\n\n# Verify CRDs are installed\nkubectl get crd | grep agentcube\n\n# Apply AgentCube deployment\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n\n# Verify deployment\nkubectl get pods -n agentcube-system\n```\n\n### Step 7: Wait for AgentCube to be Ready\n\n```bash\n# Wait for deployment to be ready\nkubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n    deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n\n# Verify all pods are running\nkubectl get pods -n agentcube-system\n```\n\nExpected output:\n```\nNAME                                         READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\nagentcube-controller-manager-7f8b9c9d4-abc12   1/1     Running   0          1m\n```\n\n### Step 8: Verify Cluster Access\n\n```bash\n# Test cluster access\nkubectl get nodes\n\n# Test AgentCube CRDs\nkubectl api-resources | grep agentcube\n\n# Expected output:\n# agentruntimes                   runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1   false        AgentRuntime\n# codeinterpreters                runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1   false        CodeInterpreter\n```\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Quick Start - Run All Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all E2E tests with verbose output\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n```\n\n### Run Specific Test Suites\n\n#### AgentRuntime Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all AgentRuntime E2E tests\ngo test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run specific AgentRuntime test\ngo test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -v -ginkgo.focus=\"AgentRuntime Creation\"\n\n# Run AgentRuntime tests with timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -v -timeout 20m\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all CodeInterpreter E2E tests\ngo test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/ -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run specific CodeInterpreter test\ngo test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/ -v -ginkgo.focus=\"Code Execution\"\n\n# Run CodeInterpreter tests with timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/ -v -timeout 20m\n```\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all integration tests\ngo test ./test/e2e/integration/ -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run specific integration test\ngo test ./test/e2e/integration/ -v -ginkgo.focus=\"Workflow Integration\"\n\n# Run integration tests with timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/integration/ -v -timeout 30m\n```\n\n### Running Tests with Options\n\n#### Verbose Output\n\n```bash\n# Verbose Ginkgo output\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Show node events\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -ginkgo.showNodeEvents\n\n# Show progress\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -ginkgo.showCurrentSpecsProgress\n```\n\n#### Focus and Skip\n\n```bash\n# Focus on tests matching pattern\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.focus=\"AgentRuntime.*Creation\"\n\n# Skip tests matching pattern\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.skip=\"Concurrent\"\n\n# Focus on slow tests\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.focus=\"Slow\"\n```\n\n#### Race Detector\n\n```bash\n# Run tests with race detector\ngo test -race ./test/e2e/...\n```\n\n#### Coverage\n\n```bash\n# Generate coverage report\ngo test -cover ./test/e2e/...\n\n# Generate coverage file\ngo test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./test/e2e/...\n\n# Generate HTML coverage report\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n\n# View coverage in browser\nopen coverage.html\n```\n\n#### Timeout\n\n```bash\n# Set custom timeout (default is 10m)\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -timeout 30m\n\n# Set shorter timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -timeout 15m\n```\n\n#### Skip Cleanup\n\n```bash\n# Skip cleanup to preserve test resources for debugging\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -skip-cleanup=true\n```\n\n### Running Tests in Parallel\n\n```bash\n# Run tests in parallel (default)\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.parallel-procs=4\n\n# Run tests serially\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.parallel-procs=1\n\n# Run tests with custom parallelism\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.parallel-procs=2\n```\n\n### Test Filtering\n\n```bash\n# Run tests by label\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.label=\"e2e\"\n\n# Run tests by context\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.focus=\"AgentRuntime Creation\"\n\n# Run multiple patterns\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.focus=\"Creation|Invocation\"\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Cluster Not Ready\n\n**Problem**: Tests fail because cluster is not ready\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Check cluster status\nkubectl get nodes\n\n# Check AgentCube deployment\nkubectl get pods -n agentcube-system\n\n# Check pod logs\nkubectl logs -n agentcube-system deployment/agentcube-controller-manager\n\n# Wait for deployment\nkubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=10m \\\n    deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n```\n\n### Image Not Found\n\n**Problem**: Tests fail with \"ImagePullBackOff\" error\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Load images into cluster\nkind load docker-image agentcube:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-workload-manager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-picod:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Verify images\ndocker exec agentcube-e2e-control-plane crictl images | grep agentcube\n```\n\n### Timeout Errors\n\n**Problem**: Tests timeout after 10 minutes\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Increase timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -timeout 30m\n\n# Or run specific test suite with longer timeout\ngo test ./test/e2e/integration/ -v -timeout 45m\n```\n\n### Resource Not Found\n\n**Problem**: Tests fail with \"resource not found\" error\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Check resource names and namespace\nkubectl get agentruntimes -A\nkubectl get codeinterpreters -A\n\n# Check test namespace\nkubectl get namespace | grep e2e\n\n# View resource details\nkubectl describe agentruntime <name> -n <namespace>\n```\n\n### Pod Not Starting\n\n**Problem**: Pods are stuck in Pending or CrashLoopBackOff state\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Check pod status\nkubectl get pods -n <test-namespace>\n\n# Check pod logs\nkubectl logs <pod-name> -n <test-namespace>\n\n# Check pod events\nkubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <test-namespace>\n\n# Check node resources\nkubectl describe nodes\n```\n\n### Test Isolation Issues\n\n**Problem**: Tests interfere with each other\n\n**Solution**:\n```bash\n# Run tests serially\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.parallel-procs=1\n\n# Or run tests with unique namespaces (default behavior)\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.randomizeAllSpecs\n```\n\n## Test Results Interpretation\n\n### Understanding Test Output\n\n```\nRunning Suite: AgentRuntime E2E\n===============================\n\nRandom Seed: 1699999999\n\nWill run 15 specs\n\n•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••\n------------------------------[ BEFORE SUITE ]\n------------------------------[ BEFORE EACH ]\n\n[SLOW TEST:15.000s]\nAgentRuntime E2E\n  AgentRuntime Creation\n    [It] should create AgentRuntime successfully\n```\n\n**Legend**:\n- `•` = Test passed\n- `F` = Test failed\n- `P` = Test was pending\n- `[SLOW TEST:X.XXXs]` = Test took longer than expected\n\n### Viewing Detailed Output\n\n```bash\n# Run with verbose output\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v\n\n# Run with Ginkgo verbose output\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n\n# Run with show node events\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -ginkgo.showNodeEvents\n```\n\n### Accessing Test Diagnostics\n\nWhen a test fails, diagnostics are collected:\n\n```bash\n# List diagnostic files\nls -la test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/\n\n# View pod logs\ncat test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/<test-name>-<pod-name>.log\n\n# View resource status\ncat test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/<test-name>-<timestamp>.json\n\n# View events\ncat test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/<test-name>-<timestamp>.json | jq '.events'\n```\n\n### Interpreting Failure Messages\n\n```\nExpected\n    <bool>: false\nto be true\n\nTest AgentRuntime E2E AgentRuntime Creation should apply default values failed\n```\n\n**Meaning**: The test expected `true` but got `false`. Check the test code and resource status.\n\n### Common Error Messages\n\n| Error | Meaning | Solution |\n|-------|---------|----------|\n| `timeout waiting for AgentRuntime` | Resource not ready within timeout | Increase timeout or check deployment |\n| `failed to create namespace` | Namespace already exists | Use unique namespace name |\n| `ImagePullBackOff` | Image not found | Load image into cluster |\n| `session not found` | Session was not created or was deleted | Check session creation and lifecycle |\n| `connection refused` | Service not ready | Wait for service to be ready |\n\n### Success Indicators\n\nA successful test run should show:\n\n```\n•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••\nPASS\nAgentRuntime E2E 15/15 specs •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• 0.000s\n```\n\n## Cleanup\n\nAfter running tests, you may want to clean up:\n\n```bash\n# Delete test namespaces\nkubectl delete namespace -l test=e2e\n\n# Delete kind cluster\nkind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Or keep cluster for reuse\n```\n\n## Tips and Best Practices\n\n1. **Always clean up**: Delete test resources after running tests\n2. **Use unique names**: Each test should use unique resource names\n3. **Handle failures**: Check test output and diagnostics when tests fail\n4. **Parallel execution**: Run tests in parallel for faster feedback\n5. **Timeouts**: Use appropriate timeouts for different test types\n6. **Isolation**: Ensure tests are independent and can run in any order\n\n## Additional Resources\n\n- [Ginkgo Documentation](https://onsi.github.io/ginkgo/)\n- [Gomega Documentation](https://onsi.github.io/gomega/)\n- [kind Documentation](https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/)\n- [kubectl Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/)\n- [AgentCube README](../../README.md)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go\">\nERROR [23:2] could not import k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\")\nERROR [24:2] could not import k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\")\nERROR [25:2] could not import k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/serializer (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/serializer\")\nERROR [26:14] could not import k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\")\nERROR [27:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/discovery (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/client-go/discovery\")\nERROR [28:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/discovery/cached/memory (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/client-go/discovery/cached/memory\")\nERROR [29:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/dynamic (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\")\nERROR [30:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\")\nERROR [31:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/rest (no required module provides package \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\")\nERROR [32:2] could not import k8s.io/client-go/restmapper (no r